# Web design system (`apps/web`)

## Visual language

- **Typography pairing:** `Varela Round` for headings, major labels, and prominent UI copy; `Rubik` for body text, descriptive text, and data-heavy content.
- **Color system:** use golden-yellow `#FFD25A` as the only accent for active states, highlights, and primary CTAs through semantic tokens (`primary`, `ring`).
- **Surfaces:** light mode base/card are `#FFFFFF` / `#F5F5F5`; dark mode base/card are `#0D0D0D` / `#1A1A1A`.
- **Geometry:** high rounding only: cards/containers `24px‚Äì32px`; controls (buttons/inputs/nav chips) `16px‚Äì20px`.
- **Depth:** prefer soft, large-spread shadows over visible borders.
- **Textures:** use low-opacity geometric grid/checkerboard texture in primary containers where it improves depth.
- **Glass:** overlays/floating surfaces may use `backdrop-filter: blur(10px)` with semi-transparent backgrounds.
- **Icons:** use outlined line icons with consistent stroke (`1.5px‚Äì2px`); active icons get circular accent backgrounds.
- **Motion:** hover/active states should use smooth `0.3s ease-in-out` transitions.
- **Tokens:** Use semantic Tailwind colors from CSS variables in `apps/web/src/index.css` ‚Äî `background`, `foreground`, `card`, `muted`, `border`, `primary`, `destructive`, `ring`, etc. Prefer `positive`, `negative`, `warning` for money / status (supports opacity, e.g. `bg-positive/10`).
- **Avoid** ad-hoc hex/RGB in components except rare charts; document exceptions if unavoidable.

## Dark mode

- `html` uses class `dark` when the OS prefers dark (`theme.ts` + inline script in `index.html`). Style both `:root` and `.dark` token sets; do not assume light-only contrast.

## Hebrew and RTL

- Document root: **`lang="he"`**, **`dir="rtl"`** (see `index.html`).
- **User-facing strings:** Hebrew by default, including validation copy in shared Zod schemas consumed by the web app.
- **Layout:** Prefer **logical** Tailwind utilities ‚Äî `ms` / `me`, `ps` / `pe`, `text-start` / `text-end`, `rounded-s` / `rounded-e`, and `start` / `end` insets ‚Äî not physical `ml`/`mr`/`left`/`right` unless the design intentionally stays LTR (e.g. monospace URLs).
- **Icons:** Chevrons, arrows, and ‚Äúback‚Äù cues may need mirroring (`scale-x-[-1]` or equivalent) so direction matches reading order.
- **Numbers and money:** Prefer `Intl` with locale `he-IL` (or shared formatters) for amounts and currency; never use floats for persisted money ‚Äî follow domain/engineering docs.

## Layout and a11y

- Mobile-first; readable forms and lists on narrow screens; adequate touch targets.
- Semantic HTML, labels on controls, visible focus; check contrast for gold accent on both light and dark surfaces (aim for WCAG AA).

